10-23-80

The salvator salvandus --who is both Savior and ones real Self-- speaks cryptic clues in a still small inner voice in the night, recalling Self to Self, to re-collect it. It can only be heard when and where there is exact silence. It reminds the splintered, empty Self as to who it is, where it is, the true conditions under which it exists in subjugation and forgetfulness; cryptic clues by it to itself. That stir its memory. The name of the true Self, the Savior is --
